  <div class="col-9">
    <p>Hello, my name is Robert Oliver and I would like to start off by saying thank you for visiting my website!
	I am here to familiarize you with one of the worlds greatest card games; Yu-Gi-Oh! Invented in 1999 by Konami, and on
	July 7, 2009, made the Guiness World Record for most cards sold worldwide! I first got divulged into Yu-Gi-Oh! the summer
	of my 5<sup>th</sup> grade year. Some of my friends already watched the TV series, and most of them already had trading cards.
 	I finally decided to pick up a deck from my local card shop at the time, and since then, I never put it down! I am proud to say that
	I have been playing this card game for over a decade. To play, each player starts out with 8,000 Life Points, and your goal as a player
	is to get your opponent to 0 Life Points. This game is played all over the world, and competitions are held yearly to showcase cards and skill!
	I would also like to give a quick tour of the site: The table below is 2020's most expensive cards, as of September 2020. You will see the card name
	followed by the pack it was released in, and its current value in USD. The top Navigation Bar consists of a trading card rarity guide, The best acutal in-person duel
