    <h2>Accompishments</h2>
    <p> As an avid trader, I would say that my biggest accomplishment was beating our local "pay-to-win" player. This was a player that always bought booster packs and never really traded with anyone else, so they would have an advantage at all times. I was able to beat them with a crowd wathcing as well, which may have been the best part! </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="column">
    <h2>Becoming A Trader</h2>
    <p>I would say the easiest way to become a player or trader is get a hold of a deck or two. Many older players who no longer duel like to helpk the younger generation by selling their cards off at very low prices. Even though they are used, it is a great way to get a deck of your choice going. Soon enough each of those cards will be worth money!</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="column">
    <h2>Building A Good Deck</h2>
    <p>My best tip when it comes to building a good deck is patience and a good base. In order to acheive these, one must first obtain a starter deck. This is like a baseline for what kind of deck you are going to build. These decks contain "staple" cards that many variations of the deck use.</p>
